<p>Here is few lines you need to add to your .bashrc/.zshrc/.whatevershellrc:</p>
<pre tabindex="0"><code>if [[ -z &#34;$TMUX&#34; ]] &amp;&amp; [ &#34;$SSH_CONNECTION&#34; != &#34;&#34; ]; then
 tmux attach-session -t mysession || tmux new-session -s mysession
fi
</code></pre><p>These lines check if tmux session <code>mysession</code> is exist then we <code>tmux attach-session</code>
is executed. Otherwise new session with <code>mysession</code> name is created.</p>
<p>Replace <code>mysession</code> to something more meaningful.</p>